{"title_page": "Ambi Ning Vayassaytho", "text_new": "\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Ambi\n| film name      = \n| image          = Ambi Ning Vayassaytho.jpg\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = Gurudatta Ganiga\n| producer       = Jack Manju <br /> \n| writer         = \n| screenplay     = [[Sudeep]]\n| story          = [[Dhanush]]\n| based on       = ''[[Pa Paandi]]''<br /> by Dhanush\n| starring       = [[Ambareesh]]<br />[[Sudeep]]<br />[[Suhasini Maniratnam]]<br /> [[Sruthi Hariharan]]\n| music          = [[Arjun Janya]]\n| cinematography = Jebin Jacob\n| editing        = Kiran\n| released       = {{Film date|2018|09|27}}\n| studio         = Kiccha Creatiions <br /> KSK Showreel Productions\n| distributor    = \n| runtime        = \n| country        = India\n| language       = Kannada\n| budget         = {{INR}}6 crores\n| gross          = {{INR}}25crores\n|}}\n\n'''''Ambi Ning Vayassaytho''''' ({{trans|Ambi, you have aged}}) is a 2018 Indian [[Kannada language|Kannada]] film directed by Gurudattha Ganiga in his directorial debut. The film features [[Ambareesh]] in the lead role, while [[Sudeep]] plays the role of Ambareesh during his young age. It is the last acting assignment of Ambareesh before his death.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/ambi-ninge-vayassaytho-the-late-ambareesh-starrer-to-be-re-released/articleshow/66850059.cms|title=Ambi Ninge Vayassaytho': The late Ambareesh starrer to be re-released|publisher=The Times of India|date=28 November 2018}}</ref> Actress [[Suhasini Maniratnam]] plays lead role opposite Ambareesh, marking their collaboration after 14 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kannada.eenaduindia.com/Entertainment/Sandalwood/2017/11/11143115/AmbareeshSuhasini-Acting-Together-After-14-Years.vpf|title=Ambareesh-Suhasini Acting Together After 14 Years|publisher= Eenadu India|date=11 November 2018}}</ref> [[Sruthi Hariharan]], [[Dileep Raj]], [[Rockline Venkatesh]] and others play the key supporting roles. The title of this film was suggested by Sudeep himself.<ref>{{cite news|title='\u0c85\u0c82\u0cac\u0cbf \u0ca8\u0cbf\u0c82\u0c97\u0ccd \u0cb5\u0caf\u0cb8\u0ccd\u0cb8\u0cbe\u0caf\u0ccd\u0ca4\u0ccb' \u0c88 \u0c9f\u0cc8\u0c9f\u0cb2\u0ccd \u0c95\u0cca\u0c9f\u0ccd\u0c9f\u0cbf\u0ca6\u0ccd\u0ca6\u0cc1 \u0caf\u0cbe\u0cb0\u0cc1?|url=https://kannada.filmibeat.com/news/a-story-behind-the-title-ambi-ninge-vayassaithu-027430.html|accessdate=24 December 2017|work=filmibeat kannada|language=Kannada}}</ref> The film is a remake of 2017 [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film ''[[Pa Paandi]]'' which was directed by actor [[Dhanush]].<ref>https://gulfnews.com/entertainment/south-indian/kannada-film-ambi-ning-vayassaytho-is-a-tamil-remake-1.2290679</ref>\n\nThe film is produced by Jack Manju & KSK Showreel Productions along with Sudeep's own banner ''Kiccha Creations''. Music for the movie is composed by [[Arjun Janya]] whilst the cinematography is by Jebin Jacob and editing by Kiran. Screenplay is written by Sudeep.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news|title=\u0c85\u0c82\u0cac\u0cbf\u0caf\u0cb2\u0ccd\u0cb2\u0cbf \u0cb8\u0cc1\u0ca6\u0cc0 \u0caa\u0cbe\u0ca4\u0ccd\u0cb0\u0c95\u0ccd\u0c95\u0cc6 \u0cb8\u0cbf\u0c9c\u0cbf \u0cb5\u0cb0\u0ccd|url=https://vijaykarnataka.indiatimes.com/entertainment/gossip/sudeep-acting-in-ambi-ninge-vayassaytho/articleshow/62008576.cms|accessdate=24 December 2017|work=Vijay Karnataka|language=Kannada}}</ref> The film was released on 27 September 2018 to a positive response from critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/ambi-ning-vayassaytho/movie-review/65978732.cms|title=Ambi Ning Vayassaytho Movie Review|publisher=The Times of India|date=27 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nIn their younger age Ambi was in love with Nandhini. Due to her father's opposition  she had to marry a boy who was chosen of her father's choice. Later unable to find his love, Ambi heads towards Bangalore and becomes a successful stunt master. The Ambi is then married to a girl of his family 's choice and marries of. She gives birth to a son.later after 20 years Ambi goes in search of Nandhini again. Will they both get united , will form the crux of the story.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Ambareesh]] as Ambareesh (Ambi)\n* [[Sudeep]] as Young Ambareesh (Ambi) \n* [[Suhasini Maniratnam]] as Nandini\n* [[Sruthi Hariharan]] as Young Nandini\n* Shivaraj KR Pete, Ambi's friend\n* [[Dileep Raj]] as Ambi's Son\n* [[Rockline Venkatesh]] as Police Officer\n* [[Doddanna]] (guest appearance )\n* [[Jai Jagadish]] (guest appearance )\n* [[Avinash]] as Nandini's Father\n* Veena Ponnappa as Ambi's Daughter in Law\n* Sangeetha as Ambi's Wife\n* Kari Subbu (guest appearance) \n* Gouthami Gowda as Nandhini's daughter \n* Ram Manjunaath as Gym Owner\n* Abhishek Das as Karthik, Ambi's neighbour\n* Geetha Bharathi Bhat as Ambi's Cousin\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nThe Trailer of this movie was released on 09th Dec 2017. Pre-production has already began with the CG- [[Computer graphics]] Work of matching Sudeep's height for Ambareesh's height for the character of younger Ambareesh. Technicians who have worked for [[Shah Rukh Khan]]\u2019s 2015 film ''[[Fan (film)|Fan]]'' have been working for this movie too.<ref name=\"auto\" />\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Ambi Ning Vayassaytho\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Arjun Janya]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 5 September 2018\n| recorded     = 2018\n| genre        = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length       = 20:20\n| label        = Anand Audio Video\n| producer     = Arjun Janya\n| prev_title   = [[The Villain (2018 film)|The Villain]]\n| prev_year    = 2018\n| next_title   = Victory 2\n| next_year    = 2018\n}}\n\n[[Arjun Janya]] has composed the soundtrack and background music for the film. The soundtrack album consists of five songs. Lyrics for the tracks were written by [[Yogaraj Bhat]], [[Prem (film director)|Jogi Prem]] and Pradyumna Narahalli.\n\n{{ tracklist\n|headline = Track-List\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 20:20\n| title1 = Jaleela\n| extra1 = [[Vijay Prakash]]\n| lyrics1 = [[Prem (film director)|Jogi Prem]]\n| length1 = 03:52\n| title2 = Mathaado Thareya\n| extra2 = Gummineni Vijay Babu\n| lyrics2 = [[V. Nagendra Prasad]]\n| length2 = 04:16\n| title3 = Oh Kshana\n| extra3 = Anirudh\n| lyrics3 = V. Nagendra Prasad\n| length3 = 04:03\n| title4 = Just Fly\n| extra4 = [[Vijay Prakash]]\n| lyrics4 = [[Chethan Kumar (director)|Chetan Kumar]]\n| length4 = 03:59\n| title5 = Ambi Ninge Vayassaytho\n| extra5 = Aadhya, Venugopal, Abhinav, Neha, Ankitha, Sanvi Shetty, Abhijath\n| lyrics5 = V. Nagendra Prasad\n| length5 = 04:10\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|7726074}}\n\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Kannada-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s coming-of-age drama films]]\n[[Category:Kannada remakes of Tamil films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Arjun Janya]]\n[[Category:Indian coming-of-age films]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:2018 directorial debut films]]\n[[Category:2010s comedy-drama films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|{{notability|1=Films|date=December 2017}}{{unreliable sources|date=December 2017}}}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Ambi Ning Vayassaytho\n| film name      = \n| image          = Ambi Ning Vayassaytho.jpg\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = Gurudatta Ganiga\n| producer       = Jack Manju <br /> \n| writer         = \n| screenplay     = [[Sudeep]]\n| story          = [[Dhanush]]\n| based on       = ''[[Pa Paandi]]''<br /> by Dhanush\n| starring       = [[Ambareesh]]<br />[[Sudeep]]<br />[[Suhasini Maniratnam]]<br /> [[Sruthi Hariharan]]\n| music          = [[Arjun Janya]]\n| cinematography = Jebin Jacob\n| editing        = Kiran\n| released       = {{Film date|2018|09|27}}\n| studio         = Kiccha Creatiions <br /> KSK Showreel Productions\n| distributor    = \n| runtime        = \n| country        = India\n| language       = Kannada\n| budget         = {{INR}}6 crores\n| gross          = {{INR}}11crores\n|}}\n\n'''''Ambi Ning Vayassaytho''''' ({{trans|Ambi, you have aged}}) is a 2018 Indian [[Kannada language|Kannada]] film directed by Gurudattha Ganiga in his directorial debut. The film features [[Ambareesh]] in the lead role, while [[Sudeep]] plays the role of Ambareesh during his young age. It is the last acting assignment of Ambareesh before his death.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/ambi-ninge-vayassaytho-the-late-ambareesh-starrer-to-be-re-released/articleshow/66850059.cms|title=Ambi Ninge Vayassaytho': The late Ambareesh starrer to be re-released|publisher=The Times of India|date=28 November 2018}}</ref> Actress [[Suhasini Maniratnam]] plays lead role opposite Ambareesh, marking their collaboration after 14 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kannada.eenaduindia.com/Entertainment/Sandalwood/2017/11/11143115/AmbareeshSuhasini-Acting-Together-After-14-Years.vpf|title=Ambareesh-Suhasini Acting Together After 14 Years|publisher= Eenadu India|date=11 November 2018}}</ref> [[Sruthi Hariharan]], [[Dileep Raj]], [[Rockline Venkatesh]] and others play the key supporting roles. The title of this film was suggested by Sudeep himself.<ref>{{cite news|title='\u0c85\u0c82\u0cac\u0cbf \u0ca8\u0cbf\u0c82\u0c97\u0ccd \u0cb5\u0caf\u0cb8\u0ccd\u0cb8\u0cbe\u0caf\u0ccd\u0ca4\u0ccb' \u0c88 \u0c9f\u0cc8\u0c9f\u0cb2\u0ccd \u0c95\u0cca\u0c9f\u0ccd\u0c9f\u0cbf\u0ca6\u0ccd\u0ca6\u0cc1 \u0caf\u0cbe\u0cb0\u0cc1?|url=https://kannada.filmibeat.com/news/a-story-behind-the-title-ambi-ninge-vayassaithu-027430.html|accessdate=24 December 2017|work=filmibeat kannada|language=Kannada}}</ref> The film is a remake of 2017 [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film ''[[Pa Paandi]]'' which was directed by actor [[Dhanush]].<ref>https://gulfnews.com/entertainment/south-indian/kannada-film-ambi-ning-vayassaytho-is-a-tamil-remake-1.2290679</ref>\n\nThe film is produced by Jack Manju & KSK Showreel Productions along with Sudeep's own banner ''Kiccha Creations''. Music for the movie is composed by [[Arjun Janya]] whilst the cinematography is by Jebin Jacob and editing by Kiran. Screenplay is written by Sudeep.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news|title=\u0c85\u0c82\u0cac\u0cbf\u0caf\u0cb2\u0ccd\u0cb2\u0cbf \u0cb8\u0cc1\u0ca6\u0cc0 \u0caa\u0cbe\u0ca4\u0ccd\u0cb0\u0c95\u0ccd\u0c95\u0cc6 \u0cb8\u0cbf\u0c9c\u0cbf \u0cb5\u0cb0\u0ccd|url=https://vijaykarnataka.indiatimes.com/entertainment/gossip/sudeep-acting-in-ambi-ninge-vayassaytho/articleshow/62008576.cms|accessdate=24 December 2017|work=Vijay Karnataka|language=Kannada}}</ref> The film was released on 27 September 2018 to a positive response from critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/ambi-ning-vayassaytho/movie-review/65978732.cms|title=Ambi Ning Vayassaytho Movie Review|publisher=The Times of India|date=27 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nIn their younger age Ambi was in love with Nandhini. Due to her father's opposition  she had to marry a boy who was chosen of her father's choice. Later unable to find his love, Ambi heads towards Bangalore and becomes a successful stunt master. The Ambi is then married to a girl of his family 's choice and marries of. She gives birth to a son.later after 20 years Ambi goes in search of Nandhini again. Will they both get united , will form the crux of the story.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Ambareesh]] as Ambareesh (Ambi)\n* [[Sudeep]] as Young Ambareesh (Ambi) \n* [[Suhasini Maniratnam]] as Nandini\n* [[Sruthi Hariharan]] as Young Nandini\n* Shivaraj KR Pete, Ambi's friend\n* [[Dileep Raj]] as Ambi's Son\n* [[Rockline Venkatesh]] as Police Officer\n* [[Doddanna]] (guest appearance )\n* [[Jai Jagadish]] (guest appearance )\n* [[Avinash]] as Nandini's Father\n* Veena Ponnappa as Ambi's Daughter in Law\n* Sangeetha as Ambi's Wife\n* Kari Subbu (guest appearance) \n* Gouthami Gowda as Nandhini's daughter \n* Ram Manjunaath as Gym Owner\n* Abhishek Das as Karthik, Ambi's neighbour\n* Geetha Bharathi Bhat as Ambi's Cousin\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nThe Trailer of this movie was released on 09th Dec 2017. Pre-production has already began with the CG- [[Computer graphics]] Work of matching Sudeep's height for Ambareesh's height for the character of younger Ambareesh. Technicians who have worked for [[Shah Rukh Khan]]\u2019s 2015 film ''[[Fan (film)|Fan]]'' have been working for this movie too.<ref name=\"auto\" />\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Ambi Ning Vayassaytho\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Arjun Janya]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 5 September 2018\n| recorded     = 2018\n| genre        = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length       = 20:20\n| label        = Anand Audio Video\n| producer     = Arjun Janya\n| prev_title   = [[The Villain (2018 film)|The Villain]]\n| prev_year    = 2018\n| next_title   = Victory 2\n| next_year    = 2018\n}}\n\n[[Arjun Janya]] has composed the soundtrack and background music for the film. The soundtrack album consists of five songs. Lyrics for the tracks were written by [[Yogaraj Bhat]], [[Prem (film director)|Jogi Prem]] and Pradyumna Narahalli.\n\n{{ tracklist\n|headline = Track-List\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 20:20\n| title1 = Jaleela\n| extra1 = [[Vijay Prakash]]\n| lyrics1 = [[Prem (film director)|Jogi Prem]]\n| length1 = 03:52\n| title2 = Mathaado Thareya\n| extra2 = Gummineni Vijay Babu\n| lyrics2 = [[V. Nagendra Prasad]]\n| length2 = 04:16\n| title3 = Oh Kshana\n| extra3 = Anirudh\n| lyrics3 = V. Nagendra Prasad\n| length3 = 04:03\n| title4 = Just Fly\n| extra4 = [[Vijay Prakash]]\n| lyrics4 = [[Chethan Kumar (director)|Chetan Kumar]]\n| length4 = 03:59\n| 