tol\"/>\n|-\n|64 Kibit\n|{{?}}\n|MOSFET\n|[[Panasonic|Matsushita]]\n|-\n|1981\n|{{?}}\n|16 Kibit\n|{{?}}\n|MOSFET\n|Texas Instruments\n|2,500&nbsp;nm\n|NMOS\n|<ref name=\"stol\"/>\n|-\n|{{dts|1981|10}}\n|{{?}}\n|4 Kibit\n|18 ns\n|MOSFET\n|Matsushita, Toshiba\n|2,000&nbsp;nm\n|CMOS\n|<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Isobe |first1=Mitsuo |last2=Uchida |first2=Yukimasa |last3=Maeguchi |first3=Kenji |last4=Mochizuki |first4=T. |last5=Kimura |first5=M. |last6=Hatano |first6=H. |last7=Mizutani |first7=Y. |last8=Tango |first8=H. |title=An 18 ns CMOS/SOS 4K static RAM |journal=[[IEEE Journal of Solid-State Circuits]] |date=October 1981 |volume=16 |issue=5 |pages=460\u2013465 |doi=10.1109/JSSC.1981.1051623|bibcode=1981IJSSC..16..460I }}</ref>\n|-\n|1982\n|{{?}}\n|64 Kibit\n|{{?}}\n|MOSFET\n|Intel\n|[[1.5 \u00b5m process|1,500 nm]]\n|NMOS (HMOS)\n|<ref name=\"stol\"/>\n|-\n|{{dts|1983|2}}\n|{{?}}\n|64 Kibit\n|50 ns\n|MOSFET\n|[[Mitsubishi Electric|Mitsubishi]]\n|{{?}}\n|CMOS\n|<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Yoshimoto |first1=M. |last2=Anami |first2=K. |last3=Shinohara |first3=H. |last4=Yoshihara |first4=T. |last5=Takagi |first5=H. |last6=Nagao |first6=S. |last7=Kayano |first7=S. |last8=Nakano |first8=T. |title=A 64Kb full CMOS RAM with divided word line structure |journal=1983 IEEE International Solid-State Circuits Conference. Digest of Technical Papers |date=1983 |volume=XXVI |pages=58\u201359 |doi=10.1109/ISSCC.1983.1156503}}</ref>\n|-\n|1984\n|{{?}}\n|256 Kibit\n|{{?}}\n|MOSFET\n|Toshiba\n|1,200&nbsp;nm\n|CMOS\n|<ref name=\"stol\"/><ref name=\"Pimbley\"/>\n|-\n|1987\n|{{?}}\n|1 [[Mebibit|Mibit]]\n|{{?}}\n|MOSFET\n|[[Sony]], Hitachi, [[Mitsubishi Electric|Mitsubishi]], Toshiba\n|{{?}}\n|CMOS\n|<ref name=\"stol\"/>\n|-\n|{{dts|1987|12}}\n|{{?}}\n|256 Kibit\n|10 ns\n|[[BiMOS]]\n|Texas Instruments\n|800 nm\n|[[BiCMOS]]\n|<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Havemann |first1=Robert H. |last2=Eklund |first2=R. E. |last3=Tran |first3=Hiep V. |last4=Haken |first4=R. A. |last5=Scott |first5=D. B. |la